# Setup

## Prerequisites

- **Python 3.11+** — the repo pins `.python-version` to 3.11.13.
- **One LLM backend:**
  - [Ollama](https://ollama.com/) for local models (recommended)
  - A [Gemini API key](https://aistudio.google.com/api-keys) if using Google's models

## Installation

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url> && cd amphib
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate       # Linux / macOS
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Pull a model (Ollama)

```bash
ollama pull gemma3:4b           # balanced — good starting point
ollama pull gemma3:12b          # more capable, needs more RAM
ollama pull gemma3:1b           # lightweight, fast
```

## Configure

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` to set your provider and credentials:

| Variable | Values | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `LLM_PROVIDER` | `ollama` or `gemini` | Which backend to use |
| `DEFAULT_MODEL` | e.g. `gemma3:4b` | Model name |
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | string | Required when using Gemini |
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | string | Optional — bumps API rate limits |

## Run

```bash
python score.py /path/to/resume.pdf
```

That's it. Amphib will parse, enrich, and print a scored evaluation.

